by Khoronzon » Wed Nov 18, 2020 3:15 pm

Hatsunia's name, like most of the nation, fundamentally mirrors the real Japan while diverging somewhat in details - its native name, Hatsune-koku, means "land of the first sound", referring to the first sound of the day due to its far-eastern location in a similar vein to how Japan's name means "origin of the sun" for much the same reason. It gained this name in the year 607, as per a letter sent to the Chinese Tang Dynasty.
